CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1772582589
OL,3,CUK economy could face 'significant
OL,4,Chit' from war in Middle-East, OBR warns
OL,6,FHigher-than-expected tax receipts - in
OL,7,Fpart due to the strong recent
OL,8,Fperformance of the stock market -
OL,9,Fenabled Rachel Reeves to pay for
OL,10,Fhigher spending on educational special
OL,11,Fneeds, fund policy U-turns on business
OL,12,Frates and inheritance tax, and cut
OL,13,Fborrowing a smidgen.
OL,15,FThe chancellor said the OBR's forecast
OL,16,Fshowed that, by the time of the next
OL,17,Felection, the average person in the UK
OL,18,Fwould be #1,000 a year better off,
OL,19,Fafter accounting for inflation, than
OL,20,Fwhen Labour was elected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1772582589
OL,3,CUK economy could face 'significant
OL,4,Chit' from war in Middle-East, OBR warns
OL,6,F"I know that the question people will
OL,7,Fask themselves at the next general
OL,8,Felection is this: Are me and my family
OL,9,Fbetter off? I am determined that the
OL,10,Fanswer will be yes," she thundered.
OL,12,FThe big issue is that the OBR's
OL,13,Fforecast was completed before a single
OL,14,Fmissile was fired at Iran and already
OL,15,Flooks out of date.
OL,17,FFinancial markets are in a state of
OL,18,Fupheaval, and investors worry about
OL,19,Fwhere the war in the Middle East is
OL,20,Fheading.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@TO]
